THIS IS THE LAST WILL AND TESTAMENT of me, {{testator}} of {{testatorCity}},
{{testatorProvince}}.

1. REVOCATION

{{#if foreignWills}}
I revoke all my prior Wills and Codicils that are intended to dispose of my property (my “Nova
Scotia Property”) situated in Nova Scotia. If I have any Wills in any jurisdiction other than Nova
Scotia (“Foreign Wills”), those Foreign Wills are not revoked by this Nova Scotia Will. The
Foreign Wills will have effect concurrently with this Nova Scotia Will, but I revoke the Foreign
Wills to the limited extent that the Foreign Wills purport to have effect in Nova Scotia or apply to
any of my Nova Scotia Property.
{{else}}
I revoke all Wills and Codicils previously made by me.
{{/if}}

{{#if marriage}}
1.1 MARRIAGE

I make this Will in contemplation of my marriage to {{intendedSpouse}}, and I declare that it is my
intention that this Will shall not be revoked by that marriage.
{{/if}}

{{#if divorce}}
1.1 DIVORCE

Notwithstanding any rule of law or statutory provision to the contrary, including Section 19A
of the Nova Scotia Wills Act, I declare that all gifts, bequests, appointments, or powers of
appointment in this Will in favor of my spouse, {{spouseName}}, and any appointment of {{spouseName}} as executor,
trustee, or in any other fiduciary capacity, shall remain valid and enforceable, even if my
marriage to {{spouseName}} is subsequently terminated by divorce or declared a nullity.
{{/if}}

2. INTERPRETATION

Where used in this document,

(a) “executor” shall be interchangeable with the term “estate trustee with a will,” shall be
deemed to include “trustee” if a trust fund has been established, to be pluralized if more than
one executor has been named, and to include all genders as the context in each case
requires;

(b) pronouns shall be construed as meaning the singular or plural, gender, personal or body
corporate as the context in each case requires and "their" may be used in place of "his" or
"her";

(c) paragraph headings are for reference purposes only and shall not define, limit, extend, or
otherwise affect the meaning of any term or provision;

(d) “divide” shall be deemed to include “pay”, “transfer” and “deliver” as the context in each
case requires;

(e) the terms “surviving”, “survivors”, "survive me", "survives me", and "survived me" shall be
deemed to include only those alive on the thirtieth day after the date of my death.

(f) “child” or “children” means surviving biological or legally adopted children, unless
otherwise specified.

(g) “sibling" or “siblings” means surviving biological siblings, unless otherwise specified.

(h) "lineal descendant or descendants" shall be deemed to include those who have been
legally adopted, unless otherwise specified.

3. APPOINTMENT OF EXECUTOR

